    "spell": {
        "name": "Beseech Arcanotheign",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "text": "With a whispered prayer or arcane sending, you conjure Arcanotheign, herald of Nethys. She's a storm of magic, half white and half black, roiling in a vaguely humanoid shape. She occupies the space of a Medium creature and has a Speed of 40 feet and a fly Speed of 60 feet.  \n  \n**Arrive** (sonic) *Storm's Unbridled Destruction* Arcanotheign arrives with a flash of light and a cacophonous crash of colliding magic. All enemies in a 60-foot emanation take 8d12 sonic damage with a basic Reflex save. A creature that critically fails is additionally deafened for 10 minutes.   \n  \n**Depart** (electricity, healing) *Flash of Brilliance* Arcanotheign fires a powerful arcane blast at one target within 100 feet, dealing 5d12 electricity damage with a basic Reflex save, and a powerful divine blast at one ally, healing 5d12 Hit Points. Then, Arcanotheign asks for payment in the form of a fond memory. If you pay this cost, you lose this memory, Arcanotheign gains this memory, and Arcanotheign whispers a secret into your mind; you can immediately Recall Knowledge on any subject at mythic proficiency.",
